==English==
===Noun===

'''recess'''

#(countable or uncountable) a [[break]], [[pause]] or [[vacation]]
#:''Spring '''recess''' offers a good chance to travel.''
#an [[inset]], [[hole]], [[space]] or [[opening]]
#:''Put a generous '''recess''' behind the handle for finger space.''
#In the United States, a time of play, usually, on a [[playground]]
#:''Students who do not listen in class will not play during '''recess'''

